     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>❧ To Nicolas Shaxton.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>If Paule had knowê it to be Gods wyll</l>
      <l>To haue this medicine put in vre:</l>
      <l>Thinke you it had passed his skill</l>
      <l>To vse the same in hys greate cure?</l>
      <l>Me durste prescribe no remedie<note place="margin">1. Cor .vil</note>
      </l>
      <l>Agaynste fleshlye incontinence:</l>
      <l>But onely chaste matrimonie,</l>
      <l>Whyche kylleth all concupiscence.</l>
      <l>Wherfore ech christian I exhorte</l>
      <l>To chose a make of honest minde</l>
      <l>To whose chaste bed they may resorte</l>
      <l>And do as nature doeth them bynde.</l>
   </lg>
   <trailer>Finis, Quod, R. C.</trailer>
</div>
